SIMPLE: excelsior
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excelsior
<hw>Ex*cel"si*or</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L., compar. of
<ets>excelsus</ets> elevated, lofty, p. p. of <ets>excellere</ets>. See
<er>Excel</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>More lofty; still higher;
ever upward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excelsior</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Excelsior
<hw>Ex*cel"si*or</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of stuffing for
upholstered furniture, mattresses, etc., in which curled shreds of wood
are substituted for curled hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excentral</ent>⟦br⟧
